# Electron Security Rules

## Critical Security Settings (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Every `BrowserWindow` MUST have:
```javascript
webPreferences: {
  nodeIntegration: false,      // Never true — XSS → RCE vector
  contextIsolation: true,      // Isolates renderer from Node.js
  sandbox: true,               // Additional OS-level sandboxing
  webSecurity: true,           // Enforces same-origin policy
  allowRunningInsecureContent: false,
  preload: path.join(__dirname, 'preload.js'),
}
```

## IPC Architecture (Mandatory)
- Renderer NEVER calls Node.js directly
- ALL cross-process communication goes through `contextBridge` in `preload.js`
- ONLY whitelisted channel names in `VALID_SEND_CHANNELS`, `VALID_INVOKE_CHANNELS`, `VALID_RECEIVE_CHANNELS`
- New IPC channels: add to whitelist in preload.js AND create handler in `ipc/` folder
- Handler modules export a `register(ipcMain)` function — main.js orchestrates registration

## External URL Handling
```javascript
// ALWAYS use this pattern — never open external URLs in the app window
win.webContents.setWindowOpenHandler(({ url }) => {
  shell.openExternal(url)
  return { action: 'deny' }
})
```

## Content Security Policy
Add to all loaded HTML:
```html
<meta http-equiv="Content-Security-Policy"
  content="default-src 'self';
           script-src 'self';
           style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline';
           connect-src 'self' http://localhost:8080 https://api.slashai.app;
           img-src 'self' data: https:;
           font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com">
```

## Token Storage
- NEVER store JWTs in `localStorage` (persists after app close, XSS accessible)
- Use `sessionStorage` for web mode (cleared on tab close)
- In Electron production: use `safeStorage.encryptString()` + OS keychain via `keytar`

## Protocol Handler
- Register custom protocol `slashai://` ONLY if deep linking is needed
- Validate all deep-link URLs before processing — treat as untrusted input

## Auto-Updater Security
- Always verify update signatures with `electron-updater`
- Use `allowPrerelease: false` in production
- Updates served over HTTPS only
